# Plan: GHCR/ORAS Nightly Distribution

Replace GitHub Releases with GitHub Container Registry (ORAS) for nightly
binary distribution. Stable releases stay on GitHub Releases as-is.

## Context

- GitHub immutable releases prevent a rolling `nightly` tag on Releases
  (can't modify assets, can't reuse tags after deletion)
- GHCR supports freely overwritable tags via OCI artifacts
- Verified locally: push, tag overwrite, anonymous pull all work
- Package `ghcr.io/getsentry/cli` is already created and public

## Key Design Decisions

- **Version discovery from manifest annotation** ‚Äî the OCI manifest has
  `annotations.version` so checking the latest nightly version needs only
  a token exchange + manifest fetch (2 requests). No need to download
  `version.json` as a blob for version checks.
- **No `jq` dependency** ‚Äî install script uses `awk -F'"'` for JSON parsing
- **Redirect quirk** ‚Äî ghcr.io blob downloads return 307 to Azure Blob
  Storage. `curl -L` forwards the auth header to Azure which returns 404.
  Must manually extract redirect URL and follow without auth.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. CI Workflow ‚Äî `publish-nightly` job

**File:** `.github/workflows/ci.yml`

- Add `packages: write` to workflow permissions
- Install `oras` CLI (single binary, ~10 MB)
- Replace `gh release create/upload` with:
  ```yaml
  oras push ghcr.io/getsentry/cli:nightly \
    --artifact-type application/vnd.sentry.cli.nightly \
    --annotation "org.opencontainers.image.source=https://github.com/getsentry/cli" \
    --annotation "version=$VERSION" \
    artifacts/*.gz \
    version.json
  ```
- Push all `.gz` binaries + `version.json` as OCI layers
- Remove dead `gh release delete/create` code and `GH_TOKEN`/`GH_REPO` env

### 2. New GHCR client module

**File:** `src/lib/ghcr.ts` (new)

Encapsulate the OCI download protocol:

- `getAnonymousToken()` ‚Äî token exchange with `ghcr.io/token`
- `fetchNightlyManifest(token)` ‚Äî OCI manifest for `:nightly` tag
- `getNightlyVersion(manifest)` ‚Äî extract from `annotations.version`
- `downloadNightlyBlob(token, manifest, filename)` ‚Äî find digest by
  `org.opencontainers.image.title` annotation, get redirect URL,
  follow without auth header
- Constants: `GHCR_REPO`, `GHCR_TAG`

### 3. Update upgrade module

**File:** `src/lib/upgrade.ts`

- Replace `fetchLatestNightlyVersion()` ‚Äî use `ghcr.ts` manifest +
  annotation (1 HTTP request after token vs 2 before)
- Replace nightly path in `downloadBinaryToTemp()` ‚Äî use `ghcr.ts` blob
  download instead of GitHub Releases URL
- Remove `NIGHTLY_TAG`, `NIGHTLY_VERSION_URL` constants
- Stable channel stays on GitHub Releases ‚Äî no changes

### 4. Update version check

**File:** `src/lib/version-check.ts`

- Calls `fetchLatestNightlyVersion()` from upgrade.ts ‚Äî should work with
  no changes after step 3. Verify.

### 5. Update install script

**File:** `install`

Replace nightly download section with GHCR flow. JSON parsing via `awk`:

```bash
# Token exchange
TOKEN=$(curl -sf "https://ghcr.io/token?scope=repository:getsentry/cli:pull" \
  | awk -F'"' '{for(i=1;i<=NF;i++) if($i=="token"){print $(i+2);exit}}')

# Manifest fetch
MANIFEST=$(curl -sf \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -H "Accept: application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json" \
  "https://ghcr.io/v2/getsentry/cli/manifests/nightly")

# Version from annotation
version=$(echo "$MANIFEST" | awk -F'"' '{for(i=1;i<=NF;i++) if($i=="version"){print $(i+2);exit}}')

# Digest for platform binary
digest=$(echo "$MANIFEST" | sed 's/},{/}\n{/g' \
  | awk -F'"' '/sentry-linux-x64\.gz/{for(i=1;i<=NF;i++) if($i=="digest"){print $(i+2);exit}}')

# Download blob (manual redirect ‚Äî don't forward auth to Azure)
redir_url=$(curl -s -w '\n%{redirect_url}' -o /dev/null \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  "https://ghcr.io/v2/getsentry/cli/blobs/$digest" | tail -1)
curl -sf "$redir_url" -o sentry.gz
```

No new dependencies ‚Äî uses only `curl`, `awk`, `sed` (all POSIX).

